eldar.com/bearwalk.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Open letter to the Dragons</span><hr size=1> Hello again Dragons,<br>
<br>
I can't believe so much happened in the few days I was away. I will address (hopefully) all the issues in this letter. I will also invite the ones who have left to come here as guests, read this letter and reply if they wish to do so, as a courtesy because in my heart they are still my dear brothers and sisters. <br>
<br>
First Issue: Guild growth<br>
-------------------------<br>
I am depply concerned with our fast growth and the loss of the family feeling. There is no easy answer though. A lot of our recruits (present and recent past) have come to us by indication of a guildmember. That means our guildmates thought DoK was a good guild to be in and wished their friends had that chance. What does that tell us? First, that a lot still consider DoK the best guild out there. Second, that these folks waiting for an invite are friends of friends. <br>
Now I don't know about you, but if I had a good friend (and I did, Nerasi, Slyde, Smiley, all friends I wanted to bring to DoK) I would like for my friend to have the best. I would like to spend all of my time with them and share a guild channel. Isn't it the way we ALL feel?<br>
Now the problem is, if each one of us has ONE friend out there we would like to guild, that would mean another 95 members for DoK. Although I agree that we are growing too fast, who can make the judgement that your friend should join the guild but someone else's friend is too many?<br>
I apologize for not being able to draw a line here. I believed everyone who ever sought DoK as an answer deserved the chance to apply and be voted on. I believed every guildmate of mine should be able to bring their friends, and their friends would become my friends. <br>
I don't know each and every one of DoK's 95 members very well. Some I have only spoken to once or twice. That isn't good. But I can't help thinking he is important to someone. If he wasn't there, someone I love and care for wouldn't be as happy. <br>
Just food for thought.<br>
As of today, there will be a recruitment freeze in DoK. The recruits we have currently are the last ones we will vote on for an indetermined period of time. Probably at least a month. The council will decide when to re-open recruitment. Please be patient if you have friends you are in the process of recruiting. <br>
<br>
Issue 2: Old Crew is leaving<br>
----------------------------<br>
I can't BEGIN to tell you how hurt I am that some folks decided to leave while I was out of town, mostly offline, and without a word to me in private. Some of these guys are old timers and I consider them personal friends. The fact that they chose to leave DoK without helping us fix what is wrong is extremely painful. I can only wish they will find happiness wherever they go, and that their friends show more consideration for their feelings than it was shown to me. DoK is a result of mine and other's hard work, time, dedication, tears, LOVE. When they were accepted into DoK, I shared my time and my thoughts with them, my RL events, I helped them as best as I could, and worked beyond whatever free time I had to ensure they had a good and organized guild structure. I do take it personally. They are friends of mine, not just members of my guild, what they do hurts me IRL not just reduces the head count in the guild. I wish they had chosen to talk to me, wait a couple of days and share their feeling with me. Even if they did leave afterwards, I would feel like they had given me a chance to help.<br>
Of the people who left - Shaedon left because he felt like I wasn't handling his issues properly. He had had serious problems with Winamin and later with Razamufin, and the fact Winamin was put on probation and not removed from the guild and Razamufin (and Shae as well, since I believed both were wrong) were issued official warnings didn't seem to be the response he was looking for. <br>
Nirron and Bollen never told me they were leaving, never bothered communicating to me or to the guild their reasons. So I didn't bother asking either. Maybe that wasn't very nice but I felt insulted by the way they just dropped out of a FAMILY. My family no less :)<br>
<br>
Issue 3: Lower Levels<br>
---------------------<br>
You are absolutely right. It seems we only do the high level stuff these days. The guild is big enough now that everyone should be able to find something to do and people to do it with. I think there is a cultural memory from when DoK was small and people are not used to taking charge and saying "ok, whoever is level 30-35 give me a tell NOW" and organizing something right there and then. I will say it again. We only seem to do high level stuff these days. But again, who should be doing the lower level stuff? The high levels? Nope. The lower levels. It's up to each one of us to organize what we want to do if nobody else is organizing. If you need my help, you will have it. No questions asked. But I'd like to see some more effort into taking grouping/raiding into your own hands. If you notice, Col and I haven't been organizing all the high level stuff. Eowen, Darkleaf, Kikulle, Phanser, these guys are taking charge and that is great :) I want to see folks like that below level 50 too!<br>
<br>
Issue 4: Colubridae<br>
--------------------<br>
Forgetting the fact Col is my husband and the most important person in the world to me. Since you don't know him as well as I do, it's easy to see only his bad temper and confrontational side. He has those allright. But he also cares deeply for this guild and does whatever he feels it's right to ensure DoK is a good guild. Sometimes he is right sometimes he is wrong. We all are. He is not an easy person to get along with (except for me :)) but he is the most loyal friend you will ever have and he will not betray you, lie to you or sugar-coat the truth. He is what he is, and that's why I love him so much. He has very strict moral rules and he is a harsh judge, but he does it not out of anger or power trips. He does it because he thinks it's right and he wants the guild to be good. I will finish here because I feel like this is something people should talk to him about individually if they have problems, but I wanted to finish by saying he was the best voted councilor for the third time in a row. (or since we started voting for council). That means (to me) that people think he is harsh, people think he has a bad temper, people think he is a hypocrat and impossible to be guilded with, but also think he is the best person to lead DoK in my absence? Weird combination.<br>
<br>
Issue 5: SOLUTIONS! (I love those)<br>
-----------------------------------<br>
Thank you so very much those who took their time to come to the board and make constructive suggestions on how to improve what we think is not good enough. Lyvja and Zavion come to mind, but I know there are others (I haven't had time to read everything yet and am already late for a meeting in Baltimore). THat's the way to go guys! Don't like it? It's fine, come and say you don't like it and we will try to fix it. But coming and saying Don't Like it, here's how it should be... THAT makes my heart sing. Because you obviously care so much about this guild that you actually think about ways to improve it and want it to be a better family. My deepest gratitude and love to you. <br>
I would like to invite all of you for a Guild Party this Sunday, at 2 pm EST (11 am Pacific) at the Lake Rathe Arena. I apologize in advance if this conflicts with something I havent looked at the calendar. But I think its important for us to bond again. A short meeting will be held as well before the tournaments and party (and salying of the beast :))<br>
I will make my own suggestions (a "zone of the week" for each level range comes to mind) when I have some more time. For now, I have to run to my meeting.<br>
<br>
Again, be assured I will do my best, give this guild all of me so we can all be happy in DoK. <br>
/guild hug<br>
<br>
I love you all <br>
<br>
<br>
