<br>
Tempestade - as always you show strong leadership - and your note here really takes the issue by the horns.<br>
<br>
I'm pretty new here; but I think one thing we all have to consider, given the way this game is designed "Size Matters".  Verant lacks the imagination to make the game more challenging to 55+ level players beyond giving mobs 35K HitPoints and Offsensive capabilities beyond what they gave "Gods" in the initial release.<br>
<br>
It's also clear that they LIKE the "Power" Guilds (I like this term better than uber) who have their ear when it comes to design etc.<br>
<br>
With Kunark - there was only one zone that was inaccessible my a mid-sized guild (Veeshan's Peak); but a good third of Velious is.  The XA is nice - but has it's limitations.  In a sense it's TOO successful - (too large) and there's the "No Clerics sign up for Fear" syndrome.<br>
<br>
IMHO there are in essence two types of guilds; "Power" Guilds and "Social" Guilds.  Clearly DOK is a Social Guild.  But these aren't either/or setups.  True Power guilds have social aspects to them.   When conflicts arise - if they aren't defused by good SOCIAL leadership they fall apart.  The people have to (to some degree) like each other.  Look at the number of guilds that rise and fall in a three week period.  Sovriegn Maxime, for example - was created and disbanded in the four weeks I've been a DoK.<br>
<br>
On the other side of the coin - unless you want to limit your capabilities; Social guilds need to have some aspects of Power Guilds.  Also - the more successful you are socially - the more popular you are.  Like Tempestade pointed out, if you have 95 people in the guild - and they all have a friend that wants to join - you soon are a 200 member guild.<br>
<br>
Inclusiveness is a GOOD thing.  I went to a VERY large University (U of Illinois) which had a large Greek System.  (My apologies to any DoK's who were in fraternaties and sororities) I dispised the attitudes of many of the people in them - and their "We're better than everyone else" and their systems that seemed to relish being able to reject people.<br>
<br>
I hate Country Clubs (apologies to any DoKs who may belong to one) that exclude on race, religion, and social class.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that certain Power Guilds on Xegony really have an arrogant attitude that I saw in some of the fraternaties and sororties, and Country Clubs, etc.  That we are a private club<br>
<br>
Now I'm rambling on here (so what else is new) but the point I'm making; If DoK is the type of organization I believe it is; it will accept anyone with open arms who simply wants to be here, shares the VALUES to be here, and demonstrates that they are willing and able to behave according to the accepted rules, and mores. It's NOT an exclusive club only open to people who heppened to sign up before 1947.<br>
<br>
I understand the need to control growth; and if a recruitment freeze needs to be done for a while - then putting people's admission on hold is a good idea.<br>
<br>
The recuritment system is a good one.  You have to wait a week and get 10 members to approve.  Perhaps it should be tweaked?  I don't think so but it could be considered...<br>
<br>
Okay bottom line time.  There's no doubt in my mind DoK is the best server on the guild.  That's why I wanted to join.  I know that bringing 11 people with me could cause strain; and I hope that the OoN "Adoption" didn't contribute to this problem.  But I know that adding quality people to a quality guild could ONLY result in making the best guild even better.  <br>
<br>
If DoK is as good as I (and I think most people here) believe it is, and it has a policy of inclusiveness - it's INEVITABLE that it will grow to a very large size.<br>
<br>
The key is communication.  There are no problems that can't be solved if people try hard and apply themselves. <p><html>
